description._content: Catalog #: 09_02127 Title: Arthur Charles Hubert Latham Special Collection Photo North Island San Diego Date: 1911 Corporation Name: Curtiss Aeroplane and Motor Company Additional Information: Antoinette monoplanes and Curtiss Pushers (Model D) at Curtiss Aviation School on North island, San Diego, 1911. Handwritten inscription ""Glenn Curtiss Aviation Camp on North Island in 1911 had a few wooden, canvas and wire airplanes anchored in the brushland."", Hubert Latham (1883 - 1912) was a French aviation pioneer who was the first pilot to attempt to cross the English Channel, and the first to land an aircraft on a body of water.
